The paper deals with approximation algorithms for optimization problems on graphs, specifically the Arora-Rao-Vazirani SDP relaxation. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) or cs.CC (computational complexity). The paper also mentions small-set expanders and graphs of bounded threshold rank, which are topics related to graph theory and computational geometry, indicating that the paper could also belong to cs.CG (computational geometry) or cs.SI (social and information networks). Finally, the paper discusses approximation factors and eigenvalues, which are concepts related to information theory, suggesting that the paper could also belong to cs.IT (information theory).
